#note this is an absolutely fascinating decision to me. My instinct would be to cash GROSZ and ENFLAME and go up 81, but Nigel "got greedy" (his words). How on earth do you even evaluate this decision? Nigel has the two Rs for ENFLAMER, and the D hook is bad news if I have it, but it's also very unlikely that I just drew a bingo (I also didn't keep the D on my last turn!). so cashing GROSZ is not as essential as it might seem. The pool is also very vowel-heavy, so ORRT? has a good chance of balancing. Lastly ZIG has great tempo for Nigel, leaving 6 tiles in the bag, such that he will win most endgames if I play a weak bingo for 70. wow!
